metadata.name: Solace #169
metadata.description:
Solace is an algorithm that generates artworks of sand dunes. It draws hundreds of thousands of tiny points according to a probability distribution calculated from the positions of the dunes.

The logic to divide the dunes into light and dark sides is simple, but produces some interesting chaotic behaviour. These are details that weren't hard-coded but emerge organically, such as the patterns on the spines of the dunes or the stripes around their bases.

Please note that the algorithm can take some time to run, especially when the number of dunes is high.

Created by lunarean.

metadata.name: Skravert #225
metadata.description:
‘Skravert’ - Norwegian, verb, past tense. ‘The act of filling an area with lines; to shade an area’.

Skravert is a series of 320 sketches, each capturing the texture and feel of a material residing somewhere between cardboard and woolen rugs. The project is centred around rectangle subdivision and a line drawing algorithm, giving each piece its own unique expression when combined with a selection of 28 different color  palettes.  

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2021

metadata.name: Kink #71
metadata.description:
Kink is a representation of the idea that creative evolution is born from the subtle twists, turns, and kinks. 

A base element is manipulated, bent and reshaped, subjecting it to the artistic equivalent of a kink. When several such ideas converge, they give birth to a fresh concept altogether through an evolution in thought and form.

Implemented in JS, this code utilizes the Perlin.js and Simple-noise.js libraries.

Press p to save a PNG of the image in full screen. Press s to save a single complete SVG file for plotting.

And this is a redeemable project in case you’d like to receive a physical plot!

Pixel Love!

metadata.name: Life with Pets #25
metadata.description:
First of all, if you have any problems or don't like the output of this piece, I will refund tez, so please feel free to contact me if you do.

I have had my cat since this year and have gotten a lot of inspiration from her.
In fact, I was on a Leonardo da Vinci-like quest to draw an elaborate human figure based on anatomy in p5js, but one day I tried to draw a cat and that stoicism disappeared somewhere and went in a somewhat pleasant direction, resulting in this work.

I will save the drawing of elaborate human figures in p5js for future enjoyment.

2000 × 2000 px
p5js
June 9. 2024
hasaqui

metadata.name: Alien Signs #26
metadata.description: Famous in the galaxy curves are featured here. The ones that require only trigonometrical functions, thus accessible to all humanoids. Projections of pure math.
